---
import IndexLayout from "../layouts/IndexLayout.astro";
---

<IndexLayout
  title="About | Silicon Logic"
  description="About Silicon Logic, its editorial commitments, signed benchmarks, and verification practice."
  canonicalUrl="/about/"
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      Silicon Logic publishes technical reviews, signed benchmark reports, and analytical notes about AI
      hardware and inference runtimes. The site is built for readers who care less about launch-day theater and
      more about whether a result can still be understood six months later.
    </p>
    <p>
      The editorial commitment is straightforward: when a numeric benchmark claim matters, the method should be
      visible and the artifact should be verifiable. Articles may still make judgments, but the measurements
      beneath those judgments should not require trust in a private spreadsheet.
    </p>
    <p>
      The publication is written by the editorial team. Individual bylines will be filled in as articles move
      through editorial verification; this placeholder keeps the site architecture honest without inventing a
      personal masthead before launch.
    </p>
    <p>
      Start with the <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a> for the measurement contract. Signed benchmark
      articles link to run artifacts and verification instructions in the source repository so readers can trace
      a claim back to the data that produced it.
    </p>
    <p>
      Contact: <a href="mailto:editorial@siliconlogic.dev">editorial@siliconlogic.dev</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</IndexLayout>
